    fr.sorbonne_u.components.ComponentI, fr.sorbonne_u.components.cyphy.interfaces.CyPhyComponentI, HairDryerImplementationI

    public class HairDryerUser
extends fr.sorbonne_u.components.cyphy.AbstractCyPhyComponent
implements HairDryerImplementationI
    The class HairDryerUser implements a usage scenario for the hair dryer in the household energy manager project.

    Description

    This component illustrates one of the way to program a user tester, use a DEVS simulator as user model. The user actions are triggered by a simulation model which leverages the capability of a simulation model to call the component code in the context of the integration of simulators and components offered by BCM4Java-CyPhy. Hence, the component creates its simulation plug-in containing its simulator and provides methods like turnOn() that will be called by the simulator and which in turn calls the corresponding servide defined by the HairDryer component through a standard component interface.

    White-box Invariant

     invariant       accFactor > 0.0
 invariant       simArchitectureURI != null && !simArchitectureURI.isEmpty()

    Black-box Invariant

     invariant       REFLECTION_INBOUND_PORT_URI != null && !REFLECTION_INBOUND_PORT_URI.isEmpty()

    Created on : 2022-10-24

    Author:
    Jacques Malenfant
